 Position Overview 
 
 This is an exciting opportunity for a seasoned Marketing Leader with demonstrated experience and passion for B2B/Enterprise Marketing. As Director, Go-To-Market (GTM) at Sitel Group, you will be a critical member of the AmeriPac Marketing team responsible for defining, developing, and executing Sitelâ€™s GTM strategy in the region to drive revenue and increase brand awareness. Working with Sales, Solutions, and regional and corporate Marketing teams, you lead a global team of campaign managers, copywriters, and designers to identify and implement account-based marketing strategies across key sectors, products and regions. In developing go-to-market strategies, you will support product marketing, sales enablement, and case study developments. Additionally, you will care deeply about bringing together the art and science of marketing to enable B2B marketing excellence by investing and innovating in our marketing tech stack. 
 
 Core Responsibilities 
 
 Develop, manage and execute holistic GTM strategy and marketing campaigns for the products you support including key activities and budgets to support the acquisition of new customers and deliver a pipeline that creates an impact on the business bottom line and is aligned with the regionâ€™s goals. 
 Create and manage account-based marketing plans and initiatives alongside the sales team to target, personalize and influence sales targets. 
 Responsible for leading both strategy and orchestration for inbound and outbound marketing programs that drive brand awareness and lead acquisition for Sitel AmeriPac. 
 Planning, executing, and coaching team to execute GTM strategies. 
 Lead the regional marketing component of the GTM strategy and/or new product launches and cross-functional implementation of the plan. 
 A key focus will be demand generation, including the curation and development of relevant content to support your channel marketing programs, including overseeing content development, sales, enablement materials. 
 Analyze and optimize strategies and tactics to improve performance. 
 Collaborate across groups to develop product positioning and messaging that resonates with our target buyer personas while developing in-depth knowledge of products, sectors, and regions. 
 Develop ongoing nurture programs to enhance the opportunity readiness of leads. 
 Work closely with sales to gather feedback on Marketing Qualified Leads to inform programs.
 Assess the effectiveness of marketing programs and report back to the heads of marketing, product, and sales. 
 Understand and support our sales channels; develop internal tools (cheat sheets) and external collateral (brochures, videos, infographics). 
 Drive alignment amongst Product, Sales, and Marketing to ensure campaign success. 
 Curating the tech stack needed to supply the organization with the right tools and resources needed to enable execution against goals. 
 Adapt agile marketing and core project management skills leveraging our Asana project management platform. 
 Drive regional content marketing and thought leadership strategy, including launching YouTube-based video channel and accompany client newsletter. 
 Develop and manage marketing budgets to maximize ROI of all marketing spend using a data-driven approach to decision making and optimize spend, cost, and marketing ROI and KPIs across all marketing programs and tactics. 
 
 Qualifications 
 
 Minimum 7 years experience managing Go-To-Market teams. 
 A deep digital marketing experience â€“ is a must. 
 Demonstrated experience and application in targeting, campaigns, messaging, content, and mix of execution to land and deliver pipeline with proven learning. 
 Data-driven & results-oriented with a keen ability to manage projects on time, on budget with a controlled set of resources, and leverage operations tools to track campaigns & events.
 Must understand how to analyze and refine programs based on performance and results. 
 Strong written, verbal, and presentation skills. 
 Agile team player that can collaborate and build momentum.
 Strategic business partner to sales, with the ability to communicate, influence, and align. 
 Ability to lead, influence, and manage executive relationships, peer relationships, and industry relationships. 
 Working knowledge of the BPO industry is a plus. 
 Bachelorâ€™s Degree in Marketing or related field preferred. 
 Ability to travel 25%. 
 
